This is not legal advice =E2=80=94=C2=A0it is the opposite of legal advice!=
 I bet your lawyer will tell you not to lie about your bank=E2=80=99s finan=
cial health on television! =E2=80=94=C2=A0and I am not even sure I believe =
it, but I kind of believe it.
  [8]
 You are the captain of the ship, which most days is a nice job and pays we=
ll, but when the ship hits an iceberg you gotta be the last one on the brid=
ge. By which I mean that potentially committing a certain amount of securit=
ies fraud on television is one of the hazards of the job.
Similarly, if you are a bank=C2=A0regulator, then I suspect that at some le=
vel you agree with this model =E2=80=94=C2=A0if the CEO of the biggest bank=
 you regulate called you up and said =E2=80=9Cthere=E2=80=99s a run on our =
bank, I=E2=80=99m gonna go on TV and say =E2=80=98it=E2=80=99s all over, ti=
me to panic,=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D=C2=A0you would probably try to dissuade her
  [9]
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0but you=E2=80=99d never=C2=A0say=C2=A0it. You can=E2=80=99t=
 go around telling bank executives that it=E2=80=99s okay to lie about thei=
r financial health in times of panic, first of all because that=E2=80=99s f=
raud and you can=E2=80=99t really encourage fraud, but also because if you=
=C2=A0say=C2=A0it publicly then it stops=C2=A0working. You can=E2=80=99t ha=
ve a norm that is like =E2=80=9Cin a bank run, the bank can lie to you,=E2=
=80=9D because then in a bank run no one will believe the bank=E2=80=99s re=
